Ack
This should only be populated when autoreboot is enabled. It is only supported by phosphor-state-manger, other implementations like x86-power-control does not.
A check was added in both getAutomatiRetry() and setautomaticRetryAttempts() to ensure the value can only be read/set if the auto reboot policy is enabled.
Done

I think the set handler should only be called when autoreboot is enabled.

And, please give a link to the corresponding changes in phosphor-state-manager.

I will make the changes.
Link to phosphor changes. 
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-state-manager/+/53603/2
Done
These should not be changed
I was not the one who changed this. I'll try to contact whoever did and let them know.
Done
Btw, Why I am the author?
I'm sorry,probably a git mistake on my behalf. I pulled bmcweb from gerrit, so that may be the case.
Can you have a Tested statement ?
Adding one, setting up the redfish schema validator now.
Done
Made some bigger changes, testing again tomorrow.
Done
Thanks for this commit! Please be sure to not have extra changes in your commit. Please also be sure to include a Tested statement.
Why is all of this changed here?
I think I saw these changes as a separate commit as they should be. This should not be changed as part of this commit.

Maybe you just need to rebase 
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/commit/550a6bf85f81c1725b6c320a5ee419335cff2cf6
Reverted all the changed loc(other than the additions I made) to how they should be.

Yeah, you need to rebase your change onto current master, then re-submit the change.

Also, please change the author of this commit to yourself. You can `git reset HEAD~1` and then `git commit` again, or use `git commit --amend --author` to change the author of current commit.

The rebase is not working. 
I may just have to create a separate commit.
Done
Everything from this point on are fixes to remove the commit error I made.
Done
nit: seen this in a few commit messages, the "-" between each word is not needed.
Ack
Please wrap your commit message 50/72, as the developing guide asks.
Ack
Please don't hardcode a specific service name.  Use the mapper as we do elsewhere.

The object mapper was implemented in both getAutomatiRetry() and setautomaticRetryAttempts(). 

The get function I will be reworking as well since I believe that if the wrapping of the mapper that I did I did in the set function is correct then I can rework that function accordingly as well since it still has the hard coded paths.
Done
Have comments that need addressed
This patch is now working and tested.
You should throw an error response here.
Done
Now the function becomes very large, could you move these codes to a separate function so that this callback lambda can be very short.
yes, I will separate the retrieval of the reboot policy from the reboot attempts into separate functions.
Done
Please simply ignore the case that mapper cannot find any object. It's possible for a system having no service providing the interface.
Since I am reverting to the original I'm thinking the subtree here will be removed entirely.
Done
Please do not hardcode subtree index here, nobody can make sure subtree[2] is what you really want.

I was told to use the mapper. So I can do two things.
1. I can just hard code the paths for this getProperty(attempt paths)
2. I can parse the subtree for the correct service/path.
